; head width: 
<number id="3D82249AFF86BE1046BD5CB7FC72FF0B" box="[931,969,152,176]" pageId="15" pageNumber="410" value="2.3">2.3</number>
; pronotal length: 
<number id="3D82249AFF86BE1041935CB7FB08FF0B" box="[1165,1203,152,176]" pageId="15" pageNumber="410" value="2.1">2.1</number>
; pronotal width: 
<number id="3D82249AFF86BE10406F5CB8FA2CFF0B" box="[1393,1431,151,176]" pageId="15" pageNumber="410" value="6.1">6.1</number>
; abdominal width: 
<number id="3D82249AFF86BE10447D5C93FE32FF6E" box="[355,393,188,213]" pageId="15" pageNumber="410" value="5.4">5.4</number>
; length of antennal segments (I: 
<number id="3D82249AFF86BE1047E85C93FCA7FF6E" box="[758,796,188,213]" pageId="15" pageNumber="410" value="0.5">0.5</number>
; II: 
<number id="3D82249AFF86BE1046575C93FCD4FF6F" box="[841,879,188,212]" pageId="15" pageNumber="410" value="0.9">0.9</number>
; III: 
<number id="3D82249AFF86BE1046B85C93FC76FF6F" box="[934,973,188,212]" pageId="15" pageNumber="410" value="1.2">1.2</number>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF536BDFF86BE1045D95CF0FC67FDA3" blockId="15.[151,1436,151,645]" pageId="15" pageNumber="410">
Male: Pygophore with dorsal rim concave (
<figureCitation id="13712A38FF86BE1047A85CF0FCB2FF43" box="[694,777,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 39" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1908,1931]" captionTargetBox="[175,1406,923,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[154,1433,909,1888]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 39, Paraedessa silvicola sp. nov. 36 – 38 Male, pygophore; 36 — dorsal view; 37 — posterior view; 38 — ventral view. (Scale = 1 mm). 39 — Paramere, lateral view. (Scale = 0,5 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222983/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="410">
Fig. 
<number id="3D82249AFF86BE1047F25CF0FCB2FF43" box="[748,777,223,248]" pageId="15" pageNumber="410" value="36.0">36</number>
</figureCitation>
) and furrowed; posterolateral angles developed (Fisg. 36, 38). Genital cup processes subtriangular, large, shallowly concave, located lateral to proctiger (
<figureCitation id="13712A38FF86BE1041EB5D2BFAF6FEA7" box="[1269,1357,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 39" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1908,1931]" captionTargetBox="[175,1406,923,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[154,1433,909,1888]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 39, Paraedessa silvicola sp. nov. 36 – 38 Male, pygophore; 36 — dorsal view; 37 — posterior view; 38 — ventral view. (Scale = 1 mm). 39 — Paramere, lateral view. (Scale = 0,5 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222983/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="410">
Fig. 
<number id="3D82249AFF86BE1040305D2BFAF6FEA7" box="[1326,1357,260,284]" pageId="15" pageNumber="410" value="37.0">37</number>
</figureCitation>
); apex posteriorly projected and surpassing dorsal rim in lateral view (
<figureCitation id="13712A38FF86BE1046475D08FC59FEFB" box="[857,994,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 39" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1908,1931]" captionTargetBox="[175,1406,923,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[154,1433,909,1888]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 39, Paraedessa silvicola sp. nov. 36 – 38 Male, pygophore; 36 — dorsal view; 37 — posterior view; 38 — ventral view. (Scale = 1 mm). 39 — Paramere, lateral view. (Scale = 0,5 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222983/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="410">
Figs. 
<number id="3D82249AFF86BE1046895D08FC59FEFB" box="[919,994,295,320]" pageId="15" pageNumber="410" value="36.5" valueMax="37.0" valueMin="36.0">36–37</number>
</figureCitation>
). Parameres flat, subtriangular; anterior expansion triangular and large, distal margin sloping, distal expansion truncate and directed lateroposteriorly; apex expanded downwards and not surpassing dorsal rim (
<figureCitation id="13712A38FF86BE1047E45D40FC3CFE33" box="[762,903,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 39" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1908,1931]" captionTargetBox="[175,1406,923,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[154,1433,909,1888]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 39, Paraedessa silvicola sp. nov. 36 – 38 Male, pygophore; 36 — dorsal view; 37 — posterior view; 38 — ventral view. (Scale = 1 mm). 39 — Paramere, lateral view. (Scale = 0,5 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222983/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="410">Figs. 37, 39</figureCitation>
). Dorsal face of the proctiger as long as wide, whole, without a distal shallow concavity (
<figureCitation id="13712A38FF86BE1047665DBBFCB9FE16" box="[632,770,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 39" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1908,1931]" captionTargetBox="[175,1406,923,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[154,1433,909,1888]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 39, Paraedessa silvicola sp. nov. 36 – 38 Male, pygophore; 36 — dorsal view; 37 — posterior view; 38 — ventral view. (Scale = 1 mm). 39 — Paramere, lateral view. (Scale = 0,5 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222983/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="410">
Figs. 
<number id="3D82249AFF86BE1047A65DBBFCB9FE16" box="[696,770,404,429]" pageId="15" pageNumber="410" value="36.5" valueMax="37.0" valueMin="36.0">36–37</number>
</figureCitation>
). Lateral face of the proctiger slightly constricted (
<figureCitation id="13712A38FF86BE1040255DBBFA2BFE16" box="[1339,1424,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 39" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1908,1931]" captionTargetBox="[175,1406,923,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[154,1433,909,1888]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 39, Paraedessa silvicola sp. nov. 36 – 38 Male, pygophore; 36 — dorsal view; 37 — posterior view; 38 — ventral view. (Scale = 1 mm). 39 — Paramere, lateral view. (Scale = 0,5 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222983/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="410">
Fig. 
<number id="3D82249AFF86BE10406E5DBBFA2BFE16" box="[1392,1424,404,429]" pageId="15" pageNumber="410" value="36.0">36</number>
</figureCitation>
). Lateral expansion of proctiger trapezoidal, large, three or more times wider than the anal opening, and curved; projected dorsally, beyond the dorsal face, apex of lateral arms rounded and posteriorly projected (
<figureCitation id="13712A38FF86BE10401A5DF3FA2BFE4E" box="[1284,1424,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 39" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1908,1931]" captionTargetBox="[175,1406,923,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[154,1433,909,1888]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 39, Paraedessa silvicola sp. nov. 36 – 38 Male, pygophore; 36 — dorsal view; 37 — posterior view; 38 — ventral view. (Scale = 1 mm). 39 — Paramere, lateral view. (Scale = 0,5 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222983/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="410">
Figs. 
<number id="3D82249AFF86BE10405B5DF3FA2BFE4E" box="[1349,1424,476,501]" pageId="15" pageNumber="410" value="37.0" valueMax="38.0" valueMin="36.0">36–38</number>
</figureCitation>
). Ventral rim with lobes not reaching the posterolateral angle level (
<figureCitation id="13712A38FF86BE1046625DD0FC74FDA3" box="[892,975,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 39" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1908,1931]" captionTargetBox="[175,1406,923,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[154,1433,909,1888]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 39, Paraedessa silvicola sp. nov. 36 – 38 Male, pygophore; 36 — dorsal view; 37 — posterior view; 38 — ventral view. (Scale = 1 mm). 39 — Paramere, lateral view. (Scale = 0,5 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222983/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="410">
Fig. 
<number id="3D82249AFF86BE1046AE5E2FFC74FDA3" box="[944,975,512,536]" pageId="15" pageNumber="410" value="38.0">38</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3506536FF86BE1045D95E0BFACFFDDB" pageId="15" pageNumber="410" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF536BDFF86BE1045D95E0BFACFFDDB" blockId="15.[151,1436,151,645]" pageId="15" pageNumber="410">
<emphasis id="B93EEAAFFF86BE1045D95E0BFEF4FD86" bold="true" box="[199,335,548,573]" pageId="15" pageNumber="410">Comments.</emphasis>
The new species 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D3EFF86BE10472B5E0BFC9EFD86" box="[565,805,548,573]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Paraedessa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="410" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silvicola">
<emphasis id="B93EEAAFFF86BE10472B5E0BFC9EFD86" box="[565,805,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="410">Paraedessa silvicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recognized by having posterolateral angles more developed than in other species; shape of parameres and ventral rim of the pygophore with shallow excavation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
